post_text: The Auburn Public Schools Foundation recently received a grant from the Nebraska Community Foundation in the amount of $5000. The Foundation is matching the grant 1:1 for a total of $10,000 to help purchase Chromebooks for APS students. This is the second grant the Foundation has received from NCF since March. $20,000 has been invested in the education of APS students. The district is grateful for the continued support of the Foundation. Thank you Foundation Members!

post_text:
Calvert Parents,

We are so excited for school to start! The elementary will open doors at 7:40 a.m. tomorrow, Friday, August 7th. We are asking all students to enter through their designated grade level doors, which are labeled accordingly:
Kindergarten - individual (south side) doors
1st Grade - main entrance (west) doors
2nd Grade - main entrance (west) doors
3rd Grade - north gym doors
4th Grade - south drive (alley) doors
5th Grade - back northeast doors

As a reminder, breakfast will not be served tomorrow, temperatures will be checked upon arrival, masks will be available as needed, and students will be dismissed through their designated doors at 11:15 a.m.

Thank you!

Nebraska State Education Association
July 15 at 11:34 AM ¬∑

Nebraska has been approved for the Pandemic-EBT program! That means families that were on the Free or Reduced Price Lunch (FRPL) program for the 19-20 school year are eligible to receive the cost of meals missed because of COVID-19 school closures on an EBT card. Families eligible for FRPL for the full period of school closure will receive a total of $281 for the days closed per child. Deadline is July 19th! https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

We have a huge task ahead of us in providing a safe, quality education for all students. Our "Return to School" Committee (made up of admin, teachers, custodial, kitchen, transportation, and special services) is working diligently to collaboratively plan what is best for our students and communicating that plan with our with our entire district team and community.

This week we looked at critical factors we need to consider to meet our purpose of planning and preparing for 2020-21 school year in order to provide a safe environment and quality educational opportunities for our students. #thebulldogway

Dear Students and Parents,
Due to the restrictions placed on instruction at our school we are unable to host the classroom experience for Driver Education. We do however have an opportunity for those students who wish to take this course online. The student would need to use their own tablet or computer to complete the course. It does not work through a cell phone. The cost is $39 and payable to the Auburn Public Schools. If you are interested in this online class please email: Mr. Hughes at marty.hughes@apsbulldogs.org.
There may also be an opportunity to take the driving course this next fall when school starts.
Sincerely,

Marty Hughes APS MS/HS Principal

post_text:
Dear Parents,
This article is a worthy read. It gives a name to what we are all trying to cope with "crisis education". There is no protocol or guidebook for crisis education. Crisis education is doing what we can to meet the academic and more importantly the emotional needs of our students, families, and staff. We are all in this together and together we will survive day by day, hour by hour. Be kind to yourself. Your heart is in the right place.
https://bit.ly/3bCFajE

post_text:
Malcolm First Friday Fest March 6, 2020

Members of the Auburn Speech team travelled to Malcolm on March 6, 2020, to compete in the First Friday Fest tournament. The level of competition was outstanding. The Auburn team finished fifth in sweepstakes points with Omaha Skutt Catholic winning the Championship, Aurora finishing in the Runner-Up position, and David City Aquinas finishing in third place.

Medal winners for Auburn:

Kate Jones Fifth in Duet Acting
Sadie Shriver Fifth in Duet Acting
Paige Aue Sixth in Humorous Prose
Rehbekha Knowlton Sixth in Serious Prose
Sadie Shriver Fourth in Informative
Kate Jones Sixth in Informative

This was highly competitive tournament, and all team members performed exceptionally well!

Speech Night‚ÄîTuesday, March 10!

A military service academy open house is scheduled Saturday, March 21 in Kearney.
U.S. Rep. Adrian Smith, and U.S. Sens. Deb Fischer and Ben Sasse will be hosts. It will be from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at the Kearney Public Library.
The day presents an opportunity for young Nebraskans to learn more about the U.S. service academies and other military service possibilities.
For information about the open house or the service academy nomination process, please visit AdrianSmith.House.gov/Services/Service-Academy-Nominations.
